    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - IC BUS SERVICE MANUAL - HEATERS AND ACCESSORIES -
        TROUBLESHOOTING
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="3">
        <title>TROUBLESHOOTING</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Use the following procedure to remove the pressure-type cap from the radiator. Always allow
                        the engine to cool first. Wrap a thick, heavy cloth around the cap. Push down, loosen cap slowly
                        to the first notch position; then pause a moment. This will prevent possible scalding by hot
                        steam or water, which can cause injury and/or property damage.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <para>Typically, when a school bus does not have heat or air flow, several steps should be taken to
                eliminate the problem. Use the steps below as a guide to problem solving.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>No Heat from the Engine</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the heater hose gate valves. Make sure they are open (supply and return) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f4700176">Figure 69</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the coolant level. Make sure the coolant system is full and flowing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Touch the heater hoses and feel for heat at the engine supply hose.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the heater hose routing for kinked hose that could block coolant flow.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the booster pump is operating correctly if present (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f4700177">Figure 70</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Open the bleeder valve and check for air in the heater hose (air lock).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check engine operating temperature gauge and compare to air flow from heaters.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the butterfly valve and actuating cable for proper operation .</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f4700176" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg47/g47001d2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 68. Supply Cut-off Valve</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f4700177" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg47/g47001d3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                         scalefitheight="392px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 69. Heater Booster Pump</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>No Air Flow From Heater Vents or Ducts</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the circuit breaker or fuse.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the switch.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the blower motor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the resistor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check harness connections for open circuit.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repair any items that are not functioning as required.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Access Main Front Heater/Defroster Blower Motors and Resistors Assembly</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove all surface-mounting screws.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove lower return screws.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove driver's foot warm duct.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove screws that secure glove box.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift panel away from heater assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <para>For temperature and air cable routing refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f4700178">Figure 71.</hotlnk>
            </para>
            <figure id="f4700178" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg47/g4700178.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 70. Enlarged View Of Driver's Heater Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. BLOWER MOTOR ASSEMBLY - DEFROST</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HEATER MOTOR ASSEMBLY - HEAT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. RESISTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. HEAT COIL ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
